A protector protecting himself is also a self-visit
yes the concept of visiting is like you perform an ability that requires you to "leave your house" at night - which some roles and items can detect
self-visiting means that you do it to yourself so you never leave your house
the stalker role follows people who leave their house, so will only see people using their role or items on other people
if you do it on yourself you are not leaving your house and so you are not seen moving by the stalker
the harlot however goes into one specific house for the night and sees anyone who does something in that house
so they would see a self-visit (someone targeting themselves with an ability or item)
e.g a protector who protects themselves would show up to a harlot if the harlot checks the protector but the stalker would see them as not leaving their house
I strongly recommend you bookmark the unofficial how to play
everything you need is in there - players will always answer questions about mechanics honestly though so feel free to ask but it's good to have a reference :)
